ystem of marketing technology companies and services providers learn more about whats trending in the industry use peoplebased marketing everywhere connect with real people on any channel or device recognize understand and reach consumers everywhere they are today – and will be tomorrow manage data ethically and securely put the right protections in place to keep your customers and your brand safe from harm learn best practices for staying privacycompliant so you can market with confidence build your own open garden connect everything at the data layer learn how the right data foundation gives you the flexibility to snap in new technologies that give you a competitive advantage master the new data economy unlock new opportunities for putting data to work learn how to tap into experts who can help you buy carefully monetize effectively and share safely with partners discover what the right data foundation can do for you contact us acxiom  wikipedia acxiom from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from acxiom corp jump to navigation search acxiom corporation type public traded as nasdaq acxm sp  component founded conway arkansas  headquarters conway arkansas united states key people scott howe ceo products personicx abilitec infobase customer information infrastructure cii audience operating system aos revenue  billion usd  number of employees   website wwwacxiomcom acxiom corporation is a marketing technology and services company with offices in the united states europe asia and south america acxiom provides marketing and information management services including multichannel marketing addressable advertising and database management acxiom collects analyzes and passes customer and business information for clients helping them to target advertising campaigns and score leads contents  history  early years and founding  growth of company  recent years  overview and corporate structure  regulatory and security matters  electronic privacy information center   security breach   in popular culture  privacy  see also  notes  references  external links historyedit early years and foundingedit acxiom building in downtown little rock arkansas  founded as demographics in  by charles d ward in conway arkansas acxiom is headquartered in little rock arkansas united states the company has additional us offices in chicago illinois new york new york foster city california and nashville tennessee international offices are located in the united kingdom france germany netherlands poland australia china and brazil services are available to companies in other countries in november  acxiom completed the acquisition of buckley dement lp in may  acxiom made the announcement that it would acquire one of its competitors may  speh growth of companyedit according to wired in  acxiom has a history of making it difficult for consumers to remove themselves from acxioms marketing lists in early  acxiom acquired part of claritas a european data provider in  acxiom acquired digital impact and integrated its digital and online services into its businesscitation needed in  acxiom was a nominee for the big brother awards for worst corporate invader for a tradition of data brokering in early  emc corporation acquired acxiom’s information grid software in a  million deal however emc canceled the software purchase after  years of development because the software was not up to commercial software standards essentially giving back the grid technology software to acxiom on may   acxiom agreed to be bought by leading investment firms silver lake partners and valueact capital in an allcash deal valued at  billion including the assumption of about  million of debt on october   however a press release announced that the takeover agreement was to be terminated and charles morgan would retire as acxiom’s company leader upon the selection of a successor on january   acxiom named john meyer from alcatellucent as new ceo and president effective february   on july   acxiom acquired choicepoints database marketing solutions division adding seven clients from industries including banking insurance and media on october   acxiom announced it had entered into a contract with xsellnet to deliver and manage the distribution of realtime customer data and analytics to the retail auto dealer industry throughout the united states the collaboration is cobranded as x powered by acxiom recent yearsedit in  acxiom acquired part of godigital a brazilian direct marketing and data quality company on march   acxiom named jerry gramaglia as interim ceo on july   acxiom named marketing and advertising veteran scott e howe as the company’s chief executive officer and president on january   acxiom named warren c jenson as the company’s chief financial officer and executive vice president  in february  acxiom announced the closing of the sale of its background screening business acxiom information security services aiss on april   acxiom announced dr phil mui as the companys new chief product and engineering officer prior to joining acxiom mui was the group product manager for google analytics on may   acxiom announced that it had acquired liveramp a company spun out of rapleaf and cofounded by auren hoffman for  million according to cnbc in  acxiom was among nine companies that the federal trade commission was investigating to see how they collect and use consumer data on march   acxiom announced that it was moving its headquarters back to conway arkansas after selling is corporate office building in little rock arkansas  the building was acquired by simmons bank  on july   acxiom it outsourcing lp acxiom ito announced its sale to charlesbank capital partners and mc partners on january   acxiom it was rebranded to ensono with corporate headquarters located in downers grove il overview and corporate structureedit acxiom client base in the united states consists primarily of companies in the financial services insurance information services direct marketing media retail consumer packaged goods technology automotive healthcare travel and telecommunications industries and the government sector it has been described as one of the biggest companies youve never heard of in addition to collecting information about people the company helps marketers anticipate the needs of consumers according to the documentary the persuaders as the worlds largest processor of consumer data acxiom has identified  types of consumers with its segmentation product personicx in his  book data and goliath american privacy expert bruce schneier wrote that acxiom sells companies lists of consumers that include potential inheritor adult with senior parent as well as addresses of households with a diabetic focus or senior needs forrester research named acxiom one of the largest database marketing services and technology providers in the world and stated that the company “demonstrated surprising nimbleness in modernizing its offering and arguably leads the industry with its digital solutions” in their january  report “the forrester wave™ us database marketing service providers q   acxiom is a  billionayear company representing more than  percent of the directmarketingservices sector’s  billion in estimated annual sales regulatory and security mattersedit this article may be unbalanced towards certain viewpoints please improve the article by adding information on neglected viewpoints or discuss the issue on the talk page november  electronic privacy information center edit in  the electronic privacy information center filed a complaint before the federal trade commission against acxiom and jetblue airways alleging the companies provided consumer information to torch concepts a company hired by the united states army to determine how information from public and private records might be analyzed to help defend military bases from attack by terrorists and other adversaries according to the complaint acxioms activities constituted unfair and deceptive trade practices as acxiom has publicly represented its belief that individuals should have notice about how information about them is used and have choices about that dissemination and has stated that it does not permit clients to make nonpublic information available to individuals yet acxiom proceeded to sell information to torch concepts without obtaining consent an ability to opt out or furnishing notice to the affected consumerscitation needed the ftc took no action against acxiom which had responded that it had followed its privacy principles and was not deceptive in its business practices torch concepts was acting under contract to the department of defense in their efforts to research ways to improve military base security a company spokesman said our policy clearly states that we provide information products which include financial information social security number and other related information where permitted by law and that this information is provided to government agencies for the purposes of verifying information employment screening and assisting law enforcement security breach edit in  more than  billion customer records were stolen during the transmission of information to and from acxioms clients the information included names addresses and email addresses prosecutors described the  case against the hacker accused of stealing the data as the largest ever invasion and theft of personal data ever tried the stolen data only came to light during an investigation of a separate data theft incident based on their investigation prosecutors said there was no risk of identity theft or harm to individuals based on the breaches they also praised acxiom for being aggressive in pursuing the hackers and cooperating with authorities the positive outcome of this investigation is testament to the strong partnerships we have established with our counterparts at the headquarters and field offices of various organizations from the fbi and department of justice to the internal revenue service and us attorneys office in little rock said k c crowley special agent in charge of secret services little rock field office furthermore i commend acxiom corporation for their cooperation and responsible approach to the situation acxioms quick response in contacting federal investigators after determining there had been a network intrusion should serve as a model for others in similar circumstances the two primary hackers were sentenced to lengthy  years prison terms in popular cultureedit the company is the subject of the vienna teng song the hymn of acxiom from her  album aims privacyedit acxiom provides a way to optout here httpsisappsacxiomcomoptoutoptoutaspx see alsoedit list of companies in the united states list of sp  companies notesedit   acxiom names scott howe ceo  acxiom at fundinguniversecom  acxiomr corporation acquires buckley dement lp acquisition expands acxioms portfolio to provide data and database solutions to health care and pharmaceutical companies november   retrieved jul     acxiom to buy may  speh for  million may   retrieved jul     acxiom opts out of optout wired november   retrieved july     acxiom completes the acquisition of claritas europe press release acxiom corporation january   archived from the original on  retrieved    pi announces us big brother awards winners for  archived august   at the wayback machine  emc and acxiom partner to accelerate development and deployment of gridbased information infrastructure press release acxiom corporation january   archived from the original on  retrieved  emc acquires information grid software from acxiom   acxiom agrees to be acquired by silver lake and valueact capital for  billion press release acxiom corporation may   archived from the original on  retrieved    acxiom names john meyer as new ceo and president press release acxiom corporation january   archived from the original on  retrieved    chantal todé acxiom acquires choicepoints database marketing solutions divisio